# Sitemap & RSS freshness

Public discovery for this site comes from one source of truth:

- `src/lib/data/siteRoutes.ts` → powers `/sitemap.xml` and `/feed.xml`
- `static/llms.txt` → curated AI/index links (update when adding major public pages)

## When you change user-facing content

If you edit copy, features, SEO fields, or add/remove a public page, update discovery metadata in the **same change**:

1. Open `src/lib/data/siteRoutes.ts`
2. Set that route’s `lastmod` to today’s date as `YYYY-MM-DD` (use the user’s “Today's date” from context when available)
3. New public page? Add a `SITE_ROUTES` entry with `path`, `lastmod`, `changefreq`, `priority`, `title`, `description`
4. Should it appear in RSS? Set `inFeed: true` (main tools, about, `/addons`, each addon). Skip noisy URLs (every boss, calculator `?score=` variants)
5. New major page or addon? Add a matching link under the right section in `static/llms.txt` with an absolute `https://mrmythical.com/...` URL

## Examples

```ts
// Edited /addons and addon catalog copy today (2026-07-21)
{
  path: '/addons',
  lastmod: '2026-07-21', // bump
  // ...
}
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD — left lastmod stale after rewriting addon SEO copy
{ path: '/addons/dps-predictor', lastmod: '2026-06-01', ... }

// ✅ GOOD
{ path: '/addons/dps-predictor', lastmod: '2026-07-21', ... }
```

## Do not

- Do not use `new Date()` for sitemap `lastmod` (identical dates look auto-generated)
- Do not bump every route’s `lastmod` — only routes whose content actually changed
- Do not put private/api routes in `SITE_ROUTES` or `llms.txt`
